name: Brittney Griner
summary: Brittney Griner, the WNBA star, was arrested in Russia in February 2022 on drug charges and sentenced to nine years in prison. After months of negotiations, Griner was released in a prisoner swap for Russian arms dealer Viktor Bout. Upon her return to the United States, Griner expressed her joy and relief for the Americans who were also released in the swap. Despite her ordeal, Griner has remained resilient and has found joy in playing for Team USA in the Tokyo Olympics. Her journey has been marked by emotional highs and lows, but she has persevered through it all. Recently, Griner welcomed her first child with her wife, Cherelle, and has been an advocate for the release of other Americans held captive in Russia.

name: Sheila Jackson Lee
summary: The passing of Representative Sheila Jackson Lee has elicited an outpouring of tributes and remembrances. At a lying in state at Houston City Hall, she was fondly remembered by numerous dignitaries. Kamala Harris delivered a eulogy at her funeral, where she hailed Lee as a "force of nature" and a mentor. Harris, a longtime friend and sorority sister, also attended Lee's funeral. The community gathered in Acres Homes to honor Lee as a "tireless servant." Lee was remembered as a champion of Houston, particularly in her work on issues such as affordable housing and healthcare. Her legacy as a mentor and a "good mom" was also celebrated by friends and family.

name: Tropical Storm Florida
summary: Multiple news sources are reporting on a developing tropical disturbance in the Atlantic Ocean that is moving closer to the United States. The disturbance has the potential to strengthen into a tropical depression or storm by next week and could impact Florida as early as this weekend. Forecasters are urging residents to be prepared and monitor the storm's progress. Some experts believe the storm could develop into Tropical Storm Debby, while others warn it could become more severe. The National Hurricane Center has also upgraded the risk of a tropical storm forming and has issued alerts for Florida. The storm's path is still uncertain, but it could potentially bring heavy rain and potential flooding to Florida and other areas of the southeastern United States.
